    <string name="support_faq_title">Frequently Asked Questions</string>
    <string name="support_faq_q1">Why does AEGIS need device permissions?</string>
    <string name="support_faq_a1">AEGIS reads security-relevant device state: root status, bootloader, security patch date, and installed app list. This is required to generate a risk posture report for your organisation.</string>
    <string name="support_faq_q2">Is my data shared with third parties?</string>
    <string name="support_faq_a2">No. All data is sent only to the backend URL configured by your organisation. AEGIS does not share data with Anthropic or any third party.</string>
    <string name="support_faq_q3">How often does AEGIS scan?</string>
    <string name="support_faq_a3">Scans run automatically every 60 minutes in the background. You can trigger an immediate scan at any time from the main screen.</string>
    <string name="support_faq_q4">What is Play Integrity?</string>
    <string name="support_faq_a4">Google Play Integrity is a security API that verifies whether your device and app meet Google\'s integrity standards. AEGIS requests an integrity token as part of the security assessment.</string>
    <string name="support_faq_q5">Why is my upload status showing Failed?</string>
    <string name="support_faq_a5">Upload failures occur when the backend is unreachable or the enrollment token is invalid. Check your backend URL in Device Setup and ensure you have network connectivity.</string>
    <string name="support_faq_q6">How do I unenroll my device?</string>
    <string name="support_faq_a6">Tap "Clear Local Data" at the bottom of this screen to remove all local AEGIS data. Contact your administrator to remove the device from the backend.</string>
